# Frontend Design Rules

## REQUIRED: Read Design System First

Before planning or implementing ANY frontend design work, you MUST read:

1. **`.planning/codebase/DESIGN-SYSTEM.md`** - Complete design system guide
   - Brand colors (Navy, Bronze, Beige, Cream)
   - Typography hierarchy (serif headings, sans body)
   - Shadow tokens (soft, medium, elevated, glow, card, card-hover)
   - Transition patterns (fast, normal, slow, ease-standard)
   - Component patterns (cards, selection, avatars, buttons)
   - Golden rules (DO/DON'T)

2. **`.cursor/specs/frontend-design-enhancement-status.md`** - Implementation reference
   - Which components have been enhanced
   - Specific class patterns used
   - Technical notes for Tailwind CSS 4

## Design Token Requirements

### Shadows
- Cards: `shadow-card` base, `shadow-card-hover` on hover
- Dialogs/dropdowns: `shadow-elevated`
- Selection: `shadow-glow` (bronze glow)
- Always add `ring-1 ring-black/[0.03]` for subtle depth

### Transitions
- Always use `duration-fast`, `duration-normal`, or `duration-slow`
- Always use `ease-standard` for interactive transitions
- Never use instant transitions on interactive elements

### Colors
- Primary: Navy `#272630` (buttons, text)
- Accent: Bronze `#BCAB8A` (links, focus, selection)
- Background: White for cards, Beige `#E9E7DC` for header
- NEVER use harsh blues - use emerald/sky for status colors

### Typography
- Headings: `font-serif` class (Playfair Display)
- Body: Default sans (Inter)

## Component Patterns

### Interactive Cards
```tsx
className="hover:shadow-card-hover hover:-translate-y-0.5 transition-all duration-slow"
```

### Selection State
```tsx
className={cn("...", selected && "ring-2 ring-strong shadow-glow")}
```

### Avatar Hover
```tsx
className="transition-transform duration-fast ease-standard hover:scale-105"
```

## DO NOT

- Hardcode colors, shadows, or transition values
- Use `opacity-50` directly (use `opacity-disabled`)
- Skip hover states on interactive elements
- Use blue for accents (use bronze)
- Create components without checking existing patterns
